00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:43.215
I'm going to be
able to calculate

00:01:43.215 --> 00:01:45.380
the integral quite simply.

00:01:45.380 --> 00:01:47.940
So let's point out
first, that the normal

00:01:47.940 --> 00:01:52.420
at any point on the
surface is going

00:01:52.420 --> 00:01:59.360
to be equal to x comma
y comma 0 divided by a,

00:01:59.360 --> 00:02:01.440
where a is, again, the radius.

00:02:01.440 --> 00:02:04.390
Because in the normal, I
know there's no z-component.

00:02:04.390 --> 00:02:06.620
And I actually know it's
the same as the normal would

00:02:06.620 --> 00:02:09.100
be on a circle of radius a.

00:02:09.100 --> 00:02:12.470
And so this vector x comma
y has length a obviously,

00:02:12.470 --> 00:02:14.450
so that's why I'm dividing by a.

00:02:14.450 --> 00:02:17.000
So when I look at the
normal and I dot it with F,

00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:17.930
let's see what I get.

00:02:21.030 --> 00:02:30.310
