00:02:37.365 --> 00:02:40.190
and 0 times y, I add
those up, and I still

00:02:40.190 --> 00:02:41.620
have to divide by my a.

00:02:41.620 --> 00:02:44.129
So that's actually the vector
dotted with the normal.

00:02:44.129 --> 00:02:46.170
Now, what's a natural
parametrization to use here

00:02:46.170 --> 00:02:47.878
is obviously the
cylindrical coordinates,

00:02:47.878 --> 00:02:50.680
because I'm on a cylinder.

00:02:50.680 --> 00:02:52.410
The radius is fixed.

00:02:52.410 --> 00:02:55.127
But what I'm interested in is
changes in theta and changes

00:02:55.127 --> 00:02:55.710
in the height.

00:02:55.710 --> 00:02:59.430
So I'm going to be
interested in d theta and dz,

00:02:59.430 --> 00:03:02.180
