over the surface.

00:03:13.460 --> 00:03:16.464
And I'll put the
bounds momentarily.

00:03:16.464 --> 00:03:17.880
Actually, I should
also point out,

00:03:17.880 --> 00:03:21.540
I'm going to write x
and y in terms of theta,

00:03:21.540 --> 00:03:23.480
because now I know
what they are.

00:03:23.480 --> 00:03:29.480
x in terms of theta is a cosine
theta, and y in terms of theta

00:03:29.480 --> 00:03:31.480
is a sine theta.

00:03:31.480 --> 00:03:34.400
So when I simplify the
expression F dot n,

00:03:34.400 --> 00:03:39.380
I get z times cosine theta
for my first component.

00:03:39.380 --> 00:03:43.810
And I get a times
cosine theta sine

00:03:43.810 --> 00:03:45.210
theta for my second component.

00:03:48.800 --> 00:03:51.510
So let me maybe point
out again how I got that.

00:03:51.510 --> 00:03:53.190
Let me come over here.

00:03:53.190 --> 00:03:55.040
x is a cosine theta.

00:03:55.040 --> 00:03:58.040
So I get z times a cosine
theta divided by a.

00:03:58.040 --> 00:04:00.502
So I get z times cosine theta.

00:04:00.502 --> 00:04:04.080
x again is a cosine
theta. y is a sine theta.

00:04:04.080 --> 00:04:06.555
So I get a squared
cosine theta sine theta.

00:04:06.555 --> 00:04:09.920
And I divide by a, so I get
a single a cosine theta sine

00:04:09.920 --> 00:04:10.640
theta.

00:04:10.640 --> 00:04:18.777
And then my dS, as I mentioned
before, is a d theta dz, right?

00:04:18.777 --> 00:04:21.110
And so now I just have to
figure out the bounds in theta

00:04:21.110 --> 00:04:22.050
and the bounds in z.

00:04:22.050 --> 00:04:24.060
Well, the bounds
in z are very easy.

00:04:24.060 --> 00:04:27.400
The bounds in z
are simply 0 to h,

00:04:27.400 --> 00:04:31.870
and so I'm going to put
those here on the outside.

00:04:31.870 --> 00:04:34.310
And then the bounds in theta.

00:04:34.310 --> 00:04:36.640
Maybe it's helpful to come
over and look at my picture.

00:04:36.640 --> 00:04:40.130
This direction, in the
x-direction, is theta equals 0.

00:04:40.130 --> 00:04:42.980
When I swing around
to the y-direction,

00:04:42.980 --> 00:04:46.870
I'm at theta equals pi over 2.

00:04:46.870 --> 00:04:51.205
So I need to go from
0 to pi over 2, right?

00:04:51.205 --> 00:04:52.455
So let me come back over here.

00:04:57.110 --> 00:04:59.100
OK, so now, really,
I have a couple

00:04:59.100 --> 00:05:01.480
of constants that are letters,
but everything now, I'm

00:05:01.480 --> 00:05:02.420
ready to integrate.

00:05:02.420 --> 00:05:05.800
So a is just a constant,
and h is a constant,

00:05:05.800 --> 00:05:07.420
and z and theta
are my variables,

00:05:07.420 --> 00:05:09.800
and I can actually do this
integration quite simply.

00:05:09.800 --> 00:05:11.342
I'm not going to do
it because I know

00:05:11.342 --> 00:05:13.758
this is at this point something
