00:08:10.364 --> 00:08:12.780
And now, if we're going to
figure out the flux, of course,

00:08:12.780 --> 00:08:16.560
it's the integral of F dot n dS.

00:08:16.560 --> 00:08:19.200
And let's remind
ourselves what dS is.

00:08:19.200 --> 00:08:28.320
dS is going to be a squared
sine phi d theta d phi.

00:08:28.320 --> 00:08:30.270
You saw this in
